io.catalyze.sdk.android

Class CustomClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.catalyze.sdk.android.CatalyzeObject
      • io.catalyze.sdk.android.CustomClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class CustomClass
extends CatalyzeObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class allows you to interact with the Catalyze Custom Class API routes and easily interact with the responses from these routes. To use a Custom Class, a user authenticated instance of Custom Class must first be created by calling the static method getInstance and passing in a currently authenticated user. Next set the Custom Class name by calling setName().
    See Also:

        public void addReferenceArray(java.lang.String refName,
                     java.lang.String refID,
                     CatalyzeListener<CustomClass> callbackHandler)
        Add a new reference to the array refName. This class requires that the id be set. The id will be saved automatically if createEntry or getEntry has been called, otherwise you can set the id manually by calling setId.
        Parameters:
        refName -
        callbackHandler - CatalyzeListener that must expect a CustomClass on successful callback. The custom class instance returned will be a reference to the original Custom Class instance that this method was called upon, after it has been updated to match the server response.

      • getArrayRef

        public void getArrayRef(java.lang.String refName,
               java.lang.String refId,
               CatalyzeListener<CustomClass> callbackHandler)
        Performs api call to retrieve the a referenced array instance. The entire custom class instance referenced will be returned to the callback handler. This class requires that the id be set. The id will be saved automatically if createEntry or getEntry has been called, otherwise you can set the id manually by calling setId.
        Parameters:
        refName -
        refId -
        callbackHandler - CatalyzeListener that must expect a CustomClass on successful callback. This custom class will be a new Custom Class instance containing the information gotten from the array of references in the original Custom Class

      • updateEntry

        public void updateEntry(CatalyzeListener<CustomClass> callbackHandler)
        Perform api call to update an entry in a custom class, will write data to server as it is passed, so to do partial update first do a get. This class requires that the id be set. The id will be saved automatically if createEntry or getEntry has been called, otherwise you can set the id manually by calling setId.
        Parameters:
        callbackHandler - CatalyzeListener that must expect a CustomClass on successful callback. The custom class instance returned will be a reference to the the same instance of custom class that was used to call this method
